WEBVTT

00:11.445 --> 00:14.880
So...if that's where we started

00:14.882 --> 00:16.481
and this is the water

00:16.483 --> 00:18.350
and this is where
the humans are,

00:18.352 --> 00:21.486
then we must be arOooound...

00:21.488 --> 00:23.222
here.

00:25.458 --> 00:28.060
Jake: Oh, no! Giant Finn hand
straight ahead!

00:28.062 --> 00:29.461
[ Imitates crash ]

00:29.463 --> 00:30.462
Jake!

00:30.464 --> 00:33.332
That's not how
you navigate, man.

00:33.334 --> 00:34.900
Yeah, I know.

00:34.902 --> 00:36.335
But, what do you expect?

00:36.337 --> 00:38.303
I was afraid of the ocean
for, like, forever.

00:38.305 --> 00:41.306
Relax.
I'm a regular sea dog.

00:44.911 --> 00:47.579
Just gotta measure
the angle of the sun

00:47.581 --> 00:51.383
using my pocket sextant...

00:51.385 --> 00:55.020
then do some super-complicated
calculations...

00:55.022 --> 00:56.755
[ Mutters ]

00:56.757 --> 00:58.957
...and some plotting.

01:05.198 --> 01:07.866
And, voilÃ !
We got a course --

01:07.868 --> 01:09.534
straight through
the Sea of Sure Death.

01:09.536 --> 01:12.905
Susan,
we've got a course!

01:12.907 --> 01:13.839
Whoo!

01:13.841 --> 01:15.941
Both: Whoo!

01:15.943 --> 01:18.076
All: Whoo!

01:19.712 --> 01:22.447
Susan feel alive.

01:24.884 --> 01:26.251
Ahh!

01:26.253 --> 01:27.219
Mm.

01:27.221 --> 01:29.521
[ Dolphin chatters ]
[ Laughs ]

01:33.593 --> 01:35.027
Cool.

01:35.029 --> 01:40.966
El-le-fly, el-le-fly,
emerge from the chrysalis

01:40.968 --> 01:47.472
El-le-fly, el-le-fly,
emerge from the chrysalis

01:47.474 --> 01:50.208
Flyyyy

01:52.612 --> 01:55.047
[ Screaming ]

01:55.049 --> 01:56.415
Someone!

01:56.417 --> 01:57.316
[ Gasps ]

01:57.318 --> 01:58.984
Majestic animal
in distress!

01:58.986 --> 02:00.485
Let's go! Let's go!
Turn left!

02:00.487 --> 02:02.587
That's gonna take us
off course.

02:02.589 --> 02:05.157
Uh, helping people
comes first.

02:05.159 --> 02:08.193
[ Screaming ]

02:09.062 --> 02:10.896
[ Angry grumbling ]
We don't like you!

02:10.898 --> 02:12.664
You make us
uncomfortable!

02:14.300 --> 02:18.303
Susan does not think
this is a good idea.

02:18.305 --> 02:21.173
What?!
Yeah, Susan.

02:21.175 --> 02:26.111
What if those people need
to slay lizard to feed babies?

02:26.113 --> 02:27.512
Yeah, man,
then it'd be like

02:27.514 --> 02:29.314
you're the slayer
of babies.

02:29.316 --> 02:31.283
[ Sighs ]
So, it's up to Finn

02:31.285 --> 02:33.752
to stop that ship
all by his self.

02:33.754 --> 02:35.354
Catapult me, Jake.

02:44.697 --> 02:47.766
Sea lizard make
scary storm magic.

02:47.768 --> 02:50.635
[ People screaming ]

02:50.637 --> 02:52.571
We're gonna die!

03:04.650 --> 03:06.852
We deserved that.

03:09.989 --> 03:12.224
See?
Not good idea.

03:12.226 --> 03:15.861
Hello!
Yoo-hoo!

03:17.397 --> 03:19.197
Hi.

03:19.199 --> 03:21.333
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry about your boat.

03:21.335 --> 03:23.668
I was just trying
to get rid of those weirdos.

03:23.670 --> 03:25.404
Sorry.

03:25.406 --> 03:27.406
My name's Whipple, by the way.

03:27.408 --> 03:29.674
Um, I'm
Finn the human.

03:29.676 --> 03:31.309
Susan.

03:31.311 --> 03:33.178
And I'm the bad boy,
Jake.

03:33.180 --> 03:35.547
Were they after
your shiny, shiny pelt, Whipple?

03:35.549 --> 03:38.550
No, they said
I was annoying.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.252
All: What?

03:40.254 --> 03:41.853
That is so mean.

03:41.855 --> 03:43.321
I don't know what it is.

03:43.323 --> 03:46.191
I mean, I see those guys around
all the time.

03:46.193 --> 03:47.692
I thought they were cool.

03:47.694 --> 03:49.594
Uh-oh.
I lost the sextant.

03:49.596 --> 03:51.496
Does that mean
we're lost?

03:51.498 --> 03:53.432
It means I can't determine
our current posi--

03:53.434 --> 03:54.666
Ooh! Ooh!
Let me see!

03:54.668 --> 03:56.368
You trying
to get to this island?

03:56.370 --> 03:58.370
Pssh, I know where that is.
I can totally get you there.

03:58.372 --> 04:00.038
Without instruments?

04:00.040 --> 04:02.074
I got fish senses.

04:02.076 --> 04:04.242
Yeah, okay.
That sounds good.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.544
Good lizard.

04:05.546 --> 04:08.547
[ Gasps ]
You guys are so cool!

04:08.549 --> 04:10.882
You're cool,
Mr. Navigator.

04:10.884 --> 04:13.085
[ Giggles ]

04:13.087 --> 04:15.454
Whipple,
you're the greatest.

04:15.456 --> 04:18.690
Okay, so, but here's
the really clever part, okay?

04:18.692 --> 04:23.028
Squirrel girl wakes up
and realizes she's alone.

04:23.030 --> 04:25.363
Squirrel boy
never existed.

04:25.365 --> 04:28.133
It was all a dream.
Cool, right?

04:28.135 --> 04:30.302
Whipple,
you suck so much.

04:30.304 --> 04:32.471
And I'm thinking
the next novel in the series

04:32.473 --> 04:34.139
will center around
a married cat

04:34.141 --> 04:37.943
who has an extra-marital crush
on a handsome ape, Stanley.

04:37.945 --> 04:40.479
Or maybe Stanley's
too close to "Dan Lee."

04:40.481 --> 04:43.081
That's from my screenplay about
a hot turtle couple

04:43.083 --> 04:45.383
who go on a cross-country
road trip as a last resort

04:45.385 --> 04:46.918
to save their marriage.

04:46.920 --> 04:50.589
But then, they find out
they're actually gophers.

04:50.591 --> 04:53.825
Anyway, I'm really excited
about my kids' book, too.

04:53.827 --> 04:56.428
It's kind of a sad story
about these anthropomorphic

04:56.430 --> 04:59.331
salt and pepper shakers
who've been BFFs for life,

04:59.333 --> 05:03.101
but Pepper starts
developing feelings for Salt,

05:03.103 --> 05:04.603
and basically,
Salt never

05:04.605 --> 05:06.404
[muffled] returns them
and ends up marrying

05:06.406 --> 05:07.973
[normal]
another guy, so Pepper

05:07.975 --> 05:11.443
[muffled] starts writing stories
to try to distract himself.

05:11.445 --> 05:12.978
It's
semi-autobiographical --

05:12.980 --> 05:15.013
StOoop!!

05:15.015 --> 05:16.281
BMO?!       BMO?!

05:16.283 --> 05:17.616
You stowed away?

05:17.618 --> 05:19.784
Who cares?!
Give me the earplugs!

05:19.786 --> 05:20.852
Both: Shh!

05:20.854 --> 05:24.289
Wait. Are you guys
wearing earplugs?

05:24.291 --> 05:26.625
Uh...I mean, we were,
but it was

05:26.627 --> 05:29.027
'cause of the engine noise,
not 'cause of you.

05:29.029 --> 05:30.462
It is because of you!

05:30.464 --> 05:32.531
BMO.
He needs to be told.

05:32.533 --> 05:35.967
No one wants to hear
your ideas!

05:35.969 --> 05:40.872
I see. I thought
you guys were my friends,

05:40.874 --> 05:45.877
but you're all just
a bunch of <i>haters!</i>

05:59.025 --> 06:01.259
[ All screaming ]

06:04.230 --> 06:05.463
Nice one, Jake.

06:05.465 --> 06:07.666
I don't want
to be the boat, though.

06:07.668 --> 06:08.867
Well...

06:08.869 --> 06:10.035
you're the boat.

06:10.037 --> 06:11.403
Yeah, I know.

06:11.405 --> 06:13.772
Might as well go
full sloop then.

06:21.180 --> 06:23.848
All right.
Jake-boat away!

06:23.850 --> 06:25.483
Away!    Away!

06:25.485 --> 06:28.053
Uh, dude, I got no idea
where to head.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.855
BMO, don't you have
some kind of navigation app?

06:30.857 --> 06:32.023
No.

06:32.025 --> 06:33.892
Oh, wait. Yes, I do.

06:33.894 --> 06:36.161
[ Plink! ]

06:36.163 --> 06:37.862
What next, BMO?

06:37.864 --> 06:42.033
Cap'N Nav app says look for
a rock shaped like a chubby cat.

06:42.035 --> 06:44.202
That looks like cat.

06:44.204 --> 06:45.937
Full steam ahead.

06:45.939 --> 06:47.072
[ Fart! ]

06:47.074 --> 06:49.574
[ Laughter ]
Not like that!

06:51.110 --> 06:52.844
[ Gasps ]

06:52.846 --> 06:54.379
Mom? Dad?

06:54.381 --> 06:55.513
All: Whoa!

06:55.515 --> 06:56.915
Jake, this is
the wrong way!

06:56.917 --> 06:58.617
What are you guys
doing out there?

06:58.619 --> 07:01.119
Jake-boy, you gotta save
your pop from the deadly sea!

07:01.121 --> 07:04.623
I don't care for this
cocktail party one bit, Joshua.

07:04.625 --> 07:06.358
We got to save 'em.

07:06.360 --> 07:07.626
What are you
looking at?

07:07.628 --> 07:09.094
Don't you see
Mom and Dad?

07:09.096 --> 07:12.297
All I see is sea weeds.
You must be imagining it.

07:12.299 --> 07:13.898
I'm not imagining it!

07:13.900 --> 07:18.570
Uh-oh! We are headed towards
a scary thing!

07:18.572 --> 07:21.139
Susan,
help me push the boom.

07:21.141 --> 07:23.041
[ Both grunting ]

07:25.077 --> 07:27.112
No!

07:27.114 --> 07:29.881
[ Strains ]

07:29.883 --> 07:31.249
Use your core!

07:31.251 --> 07:34.419
Both: Aaaaaah!

07:34.421 --> 07:36.087
No!

07:36.089 --> 07:38.590
Remember
we love you!

07:38.592 --> 07:40.792
Even though you're
really letting us down.

07:40.794 --> 07:41.993
Aah!

07:45.231 --> 07:47.766
Hmm?

07:47.768 --> 07:49.934
Yipes!

07:49.936 --> 07:52.671
Jake keep talking
about dog-mom.

07:52.673 --> 07:54.906
His belly's swarming
with weird jellyfish.

07:54.908 --> 07:57.542
They must be jacking up
his perception.

08:07.453 --> 08:09.454
[ Both gasping ]

08:09.456 --> 08:11.523
Mommy,
I'm coming for you!

08:11.525 --> 08:14.459
Huh?
What happened?

08:14.461 --> 08:18.530
[ Gasps ]
Who are you?

08:18.532 --> 08:20.699
Hope you like to fly!

08:22.201 --> 08:23.501
You okay?

08:23.503 --> 08:25.970
Uh...
Susan's head hurts,

08:25.972 --> 08:29.140
but Susan's head
always hurting these days.

08:29.142 --> 08:31.609
All right.
Just another minor setback.

08:31.611 --> 08:32.777
BMO, which way?

08:32.779 --> 08:35.146
Finn,
I want to turn back.

08:35.148 --> 08:36.981
What? We can't.

08:36.983 --> 08:38.883
The annoying dragon
wrecked our boat,

08:38.885 --> 08:42.320
I got poisoned by jellyfish
and saw our dead parents.

08:42.322 --> 08:44.489
I don't see things
deescalating.

08:44.491 --> 08:46.191
It's just a small bump --

08:46.193 --> 08:47.992
a-a bunch of small bumps.

08:47.994 --> 08:50.562
No dumb island
can be worth the risk.

08:50.564 --> 08:53.665
Maybe not.
But I can't turn back.

08:53.667 --> 08:56.468
This trip means
a lot to you, huh?

08:56.470 --> 08:57.502
Yeah.

08:57.504 --> 08:58.870
Yeah, but why?

08:58.872 --> 09:01.639
Do you want to find some humans
and ditch us?

09:01.641 --> 09:04.743
No! It's just...
[ Sighs ]

09:04.745 --> 09:08.546
Okay, look --
I'm really happy in Ooo.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.014
I love our mom and dad,

09:10.016 --> 09:12.016
but I don't know squat
about humans.

09:12.018 --> 09:14.819
If I don't see this through,
part of me will always be stuck

09:14.821 --> 09:19.557
to that boom boom leaf where
Mom found me...still alone.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.893
I know exactly
how you feel.

09:21.895 --> 09:22.761
All: Aah!

09:22.763 --> 09:24.496
You were here all this time?

09:24.498 --> 09:26.664
Yeah, I was here
all this time.

09:26.666 --> 09:28.066
Sorry
I broke your boat.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.868
Sorry we said
you were annoying,

09:29.870 --> 09:32.704
or sorry for not telling you
you were annoying earlier.

09:32.706 --> 09:35.006
If you're still set
on going to that island,

09:35.008 --> 09:38.042
you should know that
that way is crazy dangerous.

09:38.044 --> 09:40.412
I'm...I'm ready.

09:40.414 --> 09:41.946
All: Us, too.

09:41.948 --> 09:45.083
Then, I can use my air bladder
to blow a mighty wind,

09:45.085 --> 09:48.019
a real big wind that'll
carry you over all the dangers.

09:48.021 --> 09:50.722
How come you didn't
do that earlier?

09:50.724 --> 09:52.357
I thought
we were having fun.

09:52.359 --> 09:55.593
Also, they say no one's faced
the island's colossus and lived.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.228
What colossus?!

09:57.230 --> 10:00.532
Beware. Beware the colossus
of the deep.

10:00.534 --> 10:02.600
That's not really an answer,
but we will.

10:02.602 --> 10:03.802
Here we go.

10:03.804 --> 10:06.571
[ Inhales deeply ]
Wait a minute!

10:06.573 --> 10:08.606
Byeee!

10:10.543 --> 10:12.744
Jake: Whoa!

10:12.746 --> 10:15.914
BMO: That's not right.

10:15.916 --> 10:17.816
Aah!

10:20.219 --> 10:21.886
Spooky.

10:22.655 --> 10:25.557
But at least I don't see
no colossus of the deep.

10:25.559 --> 10:27.525
[ Laughter ]

10:32.431 --> 10:34.265
Oh,
my glob!

10:34.267 --> 10:37.135
[ All screaming ]

10:54.186 --> 10:56.588
This party is so crazy!
